Majalisar Dinkin Duniya ta ce dubban 'yan ta'adda masu adawa da Pakistan ne a Afghanistan
ISLAMABAD -- Wani rahoton Majalisar Dinkin Duniya ya ce sama da 'yan tawayen Pakistan 6,000 ne ke boye a Afghanistan, mafi yawansu na kungiyar Taliban ta Pakistan ce da ke da alhakin kai hare-hare kan sojojin Pakistan da kuma fararen hula.
Rahoton da aka fitar a wannan makon ya ce kungiyar, da aka sani da Tehreek-e-Taliban (TTP), ta yi hulda da kungiyar Islamic State da ke Afghanistan.
Wasu daga cikin mambobin TTP har ma sun shiga kungiyar IS, wacce ke da hedkwatarta a gabashin Afghanistan.
Gwamnatin Afghanistan ba ta amsa ranar Lahadi ga buƙatun da The Associated Press ta yi na yin sharhi ba.
Rahoton ya ce kungiyar IS a Afghanistan, da aka sani da IS a lardin Khorasan, ta sha wahala sosai daga dakarun tsaro na Afghanistan da dakarun Amurka da NATO, har ma a wasu lokuta daga Taliban na Afghanistan.
Kungiyar bincike da kuma kula da takunkumi ta Majalisar Dinkin Duniya, wadda ke bin diddigin kungiyoyin 'yan ta'adda a dukan duniya, ce ta shirya rahoton.
Rahoton ya kiyasta yawan mambobin IS a Afghanistan a 2,200, kuma yayin da shugabancinsa ya ƙare, IS har yanzu tana ƙidaya a cikin shugabannin ta Abu Said Mohammad al-Khorasani ɗan ƙasar Syria.
Rahoton ya kuma ce tawagar sa ido ta samu bayanai cewa manyan kwamandojin kungiyar IS guda biyu, Abu Qutaibah da Abu Hajar al-Iraqi, sun iso Afghanistan kwanan nan daga Gabas ta Tsakiya.
"Ko da yake a cikin koma baya na yanki, (Islama) ta kasance mai iya kai hare-hare masu girma a sassa daban-daban na kasar, ciki har da Kabul.
Har ila yau, yana da nufin jawo hankalin mayakan Taliban da ke adawa da yarjejeniyar da Amurka ta yi", in ji rahoton, yana mai nuni da yarjejeniyar zaman lafiya da Amurka ta sanya hannu tare da Taliban a watan Fabrairu.
An cimma wannan yarjejeniya ne domin a ba Amurka damar kawo karshen shiga tsakani na shekaru 19 a Afghanistan, kuma tana kira ga Taliban da ta tabbatar da cewa ba za a yi amfani da yankin ta ba ta kungiyoyin ta'addanci.
Ana kuma sa ran yarjejeniyar za ta tabbatar da cikakken sa hannu na Taliban a yaki da IS.
Sashe na biyu kuma mai yiwuwa mafi mahimmanci na yarjejeniyar yana kiran tattaunawa tsakanin Taliban da jagorancin siyasa na Kabul.
A daren Asabar, Ma'aikatar Harkokin Wajen Amurka ta fitar da wata sanarwa da ta ce jakadan zaman lafiya Zalmay Khalilzad ya sake yin tafiya ta yankin yana neman fara tattaunawar, wanda aka dage akai-akai yayin da bangarorin biyu ke jayayya kan shirin sakin fursunoni.
Yarjejeniyar da Amurka ta goyi bayan ta bukaci gwamnatin Afghanistan da ta saki fursunonin Taliban 5,000 kuma Taliban ta saki ma'aikatan gwamnati da na soja 1,000 a matsayin abin da ake kira kyakkyawar niyya kafin tattaunawa.
Har zuwa yanzu gwamnatin ta ki saki kusan fursunonin Taliban 600 da ta kira manyan masu aikata laifuka kuma ta ba da madadin 'yanci.
Taliban sun ki yarda.
"Suna kusa da fara tattaunawar tsakanin 'yan Afghanistan, muhimmin mataki na gaba don kawo karshen yakin Afghanistan na shekaru 40", in ji sanarwar Ma'aikatar Harkokin Wajen Amurka.
"Ko da yake an samu ci gaba sosai wajen musayar fursunoni, batun yana bukatar ƙarin ƙoƙari don a warware shi".
Kakakin siyasar Taliban a farkon wannan makon ya ce a shirye take ta gudanar da tattaunawa da shugabannin siyasar Kabul bayan hutun Islama na Eid al-Adha a karshen watan, muddin an kammala sakin fursunoni.
Babban abin damuwa ga Pakistan shine kasancewar mayakan a Afghanistan, musamman masu alaƙa da TTP ko Jamaat-ul-Ahrar ko Lashkar-e-Islam, da waɗanda ke tare da Sojojin 'Yanci na Baluchistan, waɗanda suka ɗauki alhakin manyan hare-hare a wannan watan a lardin Sindh na kudu da kuma a lardin Baluchistan na kudu maso yamma.
An kashe sojoji da dama na Pakistan a wannan watan a lardin Baluchistan da ke kudu maso yammacin kasar a yakin da 'yan tawaye suka yi.
TTP ta dauki alhakin daya daga cikin munanan hare-hare a Pakistan a shekarar 2014, lokacin da aka kai hari a makarantar sojin Pakistan kuma aka kashe 140.
Yawancin su ɗalibai ne, wasu kuma 'yan shekara biyar ne kawai.
"Tasalin adadin 'yan ta'addan Pakistan da ke Afghanistan, wadanda ke barazana ga kasashen biyu, an kiyasta su tsakanin 6,000 da 6,500, mafi yawansu suna tare da TTP", in ji rahoton.
