Babban jami'in Majalisar Dinkin Duniya ya tsallake ziyarar Pakistan, saboda batun jirgin sama
ISLAMABAD (AP) - Shugaban Majalisar Dinkin Duniya na gaba ya sanar a ranar Lahadi cewa yana jinkirta ziyarar da aka shirya zuwa Pakistan "saboda wasu matsalolin fasaha na jirgin sama".
An zabi jami'in diflomasiyyar Turkiyya Volkan Bozkir a matsayin shugaban taron Majalisar Dinkin Duniya karo na 75 a watan da ya gabata kuma an tsara shi ya isa Islamabad a ranar Lahadi.
Amma a cikin wani sakon Twitter, ya ce ziyarar zuwa babban birnin Pakistan dole ne ya jira.
Ministan harkokin wajen Pakistan Shah Mahmood Qureshi ya wallafa a shafinsa na Twitter a matsayin martani ga Bozkir cewa "Ina fatan maraba da ku zuwa Pakistan nan ba da jimawa ba don ziyarar da za ta kasance mai ma'ana da amfani".
Kwana daya da suka gabata, wani Qureshi mai farin ciki, yayin sanar da ziyarar, ya yi fatan zai tattauna batutuwa da dama tare da Bozkir, ciki har da Kashmir, wanda aka raba tsakanin Pakistan da makwabciyar Indiya kuma duka biyun sun yi ikirarin gaba daya.
Pakistan da Indiya sun yi yaƙi biyu daga cikin yaƙinsu uku a kan yankin da ake takaddama tun lokacin da suka sami 'yanci daga mulkin Burtaniya a 1947.
Bangarorin biyu sukan yi musayar wuta a Kashmir, wanda ke haifar da asarar sojoji da fararen hula a bangarorin biyu.
Pakistan na son Majalisar Dinkin Duniya ta taka rawar ta wajen warware matsalar Kashmir a karkashin kudurunta ta hanyar bai wa mutanen da ke zaune a yankin Himalayan damar yanke shawara ko suna son haɗewa da Indiya, da Pakistan ko kuma ko sun fi son 'yancin kai.
